Hi there, we love LHC!  Thank you!!!!

Google now penalises sites in search rankings if they have a high Cumulative Layout Shift.   After much debugging, we determined that the source of the CLS on our site was the appearance of the pro-active chat invitation that we show after a few seconds on each page.

This is because when the invitation iframe is first shown, it is centred in the screen regardless of its final position, then its style is set to display: block !important, and then it is moved to its final position (in the bottom right of the window in our case).  It is the final move that causes the high CLS (greater than 0.1), because its display is already "block".

We couldn't figure out how to change the order in which this happens with the index.js logic, but we did manage to kludge-fix it by modifying design/defaultheme/js/widgetv2/index.js , which is minified so all the code is one line.

First back up this file, then find the first "show" function on the line:

{key:"show",value:function(){this.restyle("display","block !important")}}

Change to look like this:

{key:"show",value:function(){setTimeout(()=>{this.restyle("display", "block !important")}, 100)}}

The timeout of 100ms allows the iframe for the pro-active chat invitation to be moved into position before its display is set to block, thus eliminating layout shift.

This fixed the CLS but we also had to add a style for the iframe to get it to display in the right place:
<style>
#lhc_widget_v2 {
        height: auto !important;
        max-height: 145px !important;
}
</style>

I hope this helps someone!  We would have had to abandon LiveHelperChat if we hadn't figured this out, as Google search rankings are so important.
